Aldi has a number of offers in the middle aisle every week – called Specialbuys. From egg chairs to bedding, and fire pits to gin, there are always some great deals to be found. If you’re planning ahead to visit the iconic middle aisle – or you prefer to get your bargains online – we’ve got you covered. Here are our top picks of this week’s Aldi Specialbuys. This week, Aldi’s shelves are pretty much a mixed bag. There’s loads to choose from in home and garden, as well as some budget beauty products. With kids on their summer holidays, they’ll be bursting to play outside. This wooden swing is super sturdy, made with premium FSC certified timber, and has has soft feel ropes and a heavy duty moulded seat for extra strength and comfort. Buy for £110 on the Aldi website now. Aldi has just released its own range of bond-building haircare to rival Olaplex (but with a much smaller price point). At £6.98 for a shampoo and conditioner, the range promises to smooth and strengthen hair, leaving it manageable and healthy. Buy on the Aldi website and in stores now. It’s prime barbecuing weather but, let’s be honest, that’s never stopped us Brits from cracking out the grill. This option is perfect for smaller gardens, with wheels for easy portability and a storage rack to keep your utensils close to hand. Buy for £29.99 in Aldi stores only from today. Level up your movie night with this popcorn maker from Aldi. Simply add popcorn kernels using the included measuring scoop before letting it work its magic and adding any toppings. Best of all, no oil or fat is required. Buy for £19.99 on the Aldi website now, and in stores from Sunday July 31. You can order online and find more Specialbuys on the Aldi website. Follow Metro across our social channels, on Facebook, Twitter and Instagram Share your views in the comments below MORE : The most underrated city breaks you should book for your next trip MORE : The most stylish summer children’s travel wear for 2022